<h4 style="margin-bottom: 30px;"><strong>Tell us how we're doing:</strong> <a href="https://byui.qualtrics.com/SE/?SID=SV_er1KOSg3xflWYQc">Take a brief survey here</a>.</h4>
<p style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><strong>Your Rights and Responsibilities as a Patient</strong></p>
<p>As a patient at the Brigham Young University - Idaho Student Health Center</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><strong><strong>Your Rights Include:<br /><br /></strong></strong></p>
<ul style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 12pt;">
<li>The right to receive compassionate care and treatment.</li>
<li>The right to receive accurate information (to the extent known) concerning diagnosis, treatment, and prognosis of your medical condition.</li>
<li>The opportunity to obtain a second opinion, if you wish.</li>
<li>The right to participate in decisions regarding your health care and treatment.</li>
</ul>
<p style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><strong><strong>Your responsibilities include:<br /><br /></strong></strong></p>
<ul style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 12pt;">
<li>Providing honest and direct information relating to your symptoms and health needs.</li>
<li>The responsibility to follow the treatment plan that is established between you and your health care provider.</li>
<li>You have the responsibility to ask questions if you don't understand what is being explained to you, or if you are confused or concerned about any information you are receiving.</li>
<li>The responsibility to show courtesy and respect to health care personnel and other patients.</li>
</ul>
